text:
DOC: make sym-links in examples directories

Fixes #1124

Have "make html" create symbolic links to examples/nilearn_cache from all
the example subfolders nilearn_cache directory (on unix systems only, of
course). The goal being to federate the cache across all examples, in
order to minimize computation.

text:
DOC: add an example

This example should be the 2nd one in a beginner's tutorial.

[MRG+1] threshold=None does not modify datat in plot_prob_atlas function

Threshold is been set to 'auto' by default.

MAINT: decrease memory level

Too high memory_level in example was using a lot of disk space

Use diff without context in flake8_diff.sh

This is a conservative approach. This way PEP8 violations in old code
that was not changed do not create failures.

DOC: expose load_img and clean_img

Finishes fix #1116

text: DOC: point to the didactic examples
DOC: follow the change in doc layout

DOC: don't download NYU in examples

Use ADHD instead. The rational is to have less different data sources, in
order to have less stress on the download when building the docs.
BUG: try to fix circleCI failure

DOC: rewrite the parcellating section

The goal of this rewrite is to move all the code sample to the
notebook-like example, and keep only a high-level discussion in the
narrative documentation.

Indeed, modifications of the code in the examples (as in the previous
commit) cause code-rot in the narrative documentation that is very
hard to control.

ENH: add a function for localizer button task

The localizer button task is used in many examples. Here I
add a new function to fetch specifically this contrast.

Additional benefit: the fetch_localizer_contrasts can now specify
subjects as a list, and not only the maximum number (ie: less downloads
during tutorials :) )
